news.title: NGT forms panel for factual report on illegal brick kilns in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The tribunal passed the order while hearing a petition claiming illegal operation of a large number of brick kilns in the districts of Moradabad, Sambhal, Rampur and Amroha was causing "huge air pollution."

news.title: HC quashes Cochin development body's notices seeking more money for plots
news.para: A house is every citizen’s dream and it is with hard-earned money that people build homes, the court said while stating that it cannot agree to GCDA’s demand for more money from even those who bought land over 40 years ago.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board demolishes building violations in five Dadumajra flats
news.para: CHB is computing cost of demolitions, which would be recovered from the allottees and, in case of its non-payment, their allotments are liable to be cancelled.

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out 40,000 sq ft to Webasto Group in Pune
news.para: 315Work Avenue recently leased out 400 seats to Jupiter, a digital banking platform, in HSR Layout, Bengaluru.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body notification for outright sale of 46 plots
news.para: Two HIG plots in Marripalem layout will go under the hammer at a base price of 55,000, while 50,000 base price has been fixed for two plots in Madhavadhara.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body mops up Rs 2,600 crore property tax; far from Rs 4,000 crore target
news.para: According to data from BBMP, as of November 25, the civic body collected Rs 2,641 crore as property tax from four categories of buildings - residential, non-residential and residential-plus+non-residential and industrial.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA begins to grant exemption certificates to builders
news.para: The developers falling under the category can now approach the Raj-RERA to seek exemption and the authority will issue exemption certificates after charging a standard fee.

news.title: Bhopal: Special court sends Distinct Infrastructure's MD to five-year imprisonment
news.para: This company through its Managing Director, Ramakant Vijayvargiya had cheated more than 240 people by selling plots in a colony named “Panchavati Enclave” at Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh.

news.title: Hyderabad: HMDA to sell 38 land parcels on January 18, plans to net Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: The Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) is expecting to garner 2,000 crore by auctioning 38 land parcels on January 18.

news.title: Gurugram police make first arrest in Chintels Paradiso case
news.para: Amit Austin, proprietor of Manish Switchgear and Construction, will be produced in a city court on Thursday, Assistant Commissioner of Police, Udyog Vihar, Manoj Kumar said.

news.title: China Evergrande Group resumes work on pre-sold projects
news.para: Evergrande, which has been scrambling to raise funds it needs to pay its many lenders and suppliers, said it will continue to engage with its offshore creditors and hopes to reach a consensus on the terms of a restructuring plan.

news.title: China: CIFI Holdings, Agile Group to raise funds via discounted share sales
news.para: Shanghai-based CIFI, which is undergoing an offshore debt restructuring, said it would raise HK$957.6 million ($123 million) by selling shares at HK$1.14 apiece, a 14% discount to Monday's closing price.

news.title: Jaipur development body to take loan on behalf of JMRC for extension of metro
news.para: On November 21, 2022, the finance department gave clearance for construction of Line 1C of Jaipur Metro. This extension would connect a 2.26 km stretch from Badi to Transport Nagar on the Delhi-Agra Highway.

news.title: Lucknow: No houses for allottees of Rohtas Plumeria homes' P tower even after a decade
news.para: Presently, 14 projects are being rehabilitated through either the promoters or the AOA in UP. RPH is the first project under rehabilitation program in Lucknow, where pending projects will be commercialized by builder to complete it.

news.title: The great Bengaluru house hunt: Tenants in despair as rents go north
news.para: While eviction notices are being served under the pretext of rent increase, many are jostling to find a stay at an affordable rate.
